<br>
The best pickup group in my opinion is any group with a Shaman, Enchanter, and Cleric.  I LOVE having a shaman and enchanter in my group.  If I can get a Shaman and Enchanter to travel to various zones and be able to say &quot;Cleric, Shaman, Enchanter looking for 3 more...&quot;, we would be raped instantly <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Clerics are not better - I just think we are the least understood and that is what gets the reactions like what you have given.  I have tried to play every class - even at the high level.  I have had the opportunity to play friends characters and other guildies characters.  I like doing it so I get a feel for the other classes.  Even after all of that, I still think Clerics are the determining factor in 75% of what goes on in EQ.  Even in MOST pickup groups, clerics are the most requested class.  Does that make us better?  Nope.  We can still be a sucky cleric.  What that does mean is that we are an essential component to much of this game.  I know that our guild has 8 solid clerics yet we still clamor for more.  Yet, we have 2-3 Shaman and we are fine with that.  I know my good friend Gillianna gets bored if she is one of two Shaman on any given raid except for buffing times.  I've been on those same raids with 8 clerics and we are always stretched and pushed and I ALWAYS hear &quot;Clerics mana check&quot;.  Even in small groups it's the same way.<br>
<br>
As far as Necromancers healing, that is a whole different ball game.  You will never be able to heal like a Druid or Shaman and you have many ways to get your mana and health back on your own.  Necromancers are a whole different breed Llars and I would never shun them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><p>
